JOHANNESBURG - The JSE-listed commodities company Shanduka and Standard Bank are among the companies mentioned in the so-called Paradise Papers. Glencore is also named in the leaked information about offshore tax havens. READ: Offshore legal firm hacked, braces for media leaks The information relates to the elite law firm Appleby, which helps clients set up companies or trusts in overseas jurisdictions with low or zero tax rates. Being mentioned in the leaks in no way implies wrongdoing, but the leaks do mean companies' client information has been compromised. Anti-corruption activists say tax-haven activity increases inequality by allowing certain groups to evade the laws that taxpayers are normally subject to. eNCA